ex acts of writing and reading, the "dialogue of writing." Of interest to students of eighteenth-century French literature, this work is alsoimportant to those interested in contemporary literary criticisms, its theory and practice, as well as to students of Barthes, Derrida, and Beneviste. The volume also presents fascinating applications of the the though of Claude Lévi-Strauss.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDialogue. 0aFrench literaturexHistory and criticismx18th century. 0aFrench literaturexHistory and criticismy18th century. 0aFrench literaturey18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLittérature françaisexHistoire et critiquex18e siècle. 0aLittérature françaisexHistoire et critiquex18e siècle. 4aHistory. 4aLanguage Arts & Disciplines. 4aLiterary Criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / French.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920708040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889207080423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889207080/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles